{"lemma":"ثُومُ","slug":"ثُومُ","root":"ث.#.م","root_slug":"ث-_-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ث-_-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n4844"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AB%D9%8F%D9%88%D9%85%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"garlic","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"beads of silver or gold wherewith the grips of swords are decorated","tags":["collective"],"examples":[{"text":"١ سيف بلدي مفضه ببرشم فضه وتوم ومحاره وخروس فضه وكستبانه فضه مجلد مدس\n١ حربة شلكاية كبيرة مسلكة بفضه\n١ تركاس داخله سبعه حراب طبايق مسلكين بفضه\n٢ كواكب مسلكين بفضه","english":"1 native silvered sword with hilt of silver, decorative silvern beads, nacre, silver rings, a silver pommel, and tanned leather.\n1 large long jagged spear wired in silver\n1 quiver wherein there are seven short throwing spears wired with silver\n2 spears of wide and jagged blade wired with silver"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ṯūm-."},"ipa":["/θuːm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4844","headword_ar":"ثُومٌ","root":"vwm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Garlic;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"allium sativum"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Linn.;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqol","text_ar":"بَقْل"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AHn, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundant in the country of the Arabs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of two sorts; wild,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, M, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"growing in the cultivated tracts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in gardens:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the former sort is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vuwmu AlHay~api","text_ar":"ثُومُ الحَيَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and is the stronger,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and is brought from Syria:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"each of them is heating, expels flatulence and worms, and is strongly diuretic; and this is the most excellent"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"property"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is therein: it is good for obliviousness, and asthma, and chronic cough, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pain in"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the spleen and the flank, and colic, and sciatica,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (K: [in which are added many other supposed uses:]) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (AHn, M, K.) ―         -b2-  Hence, as being likened thereto, (M,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vuwmapN","text_ar":"ثُومَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (tropical:) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pommel of a sword."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K.) Whence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u vuwomapa","text_ar":"اُمُّ ثُوْمَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said to be the name of a certain woman, may mean (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sword."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b3-  [Hence, also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vuwomapu *akari rajulK","text_ar":"ثُوْمَةُ ذَكَرِ رَجُلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The glans of a man's penis"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Az, in TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TurovuwvN","text_ar":"طُرْثُوثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~uwmapu","text_ar":"الثُّومَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The channel"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oblong depression"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the two mustaches, against the partition between the two nostrils;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxunoEubapu","text_ar":"الخُنْعُبَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xnEb","text_ar":"خنعب"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vuwmN","text_ar":"ثُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwmN","text_ar":"فُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wheat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, T, M.) And the latter is used in the [ordinary] sense of the former. (T.)"}],"source_refs":["AHn","M","S","K","TA"]}]}}